WEBVTT

00:10.120 --> 00:16.668
I am, beyond a doubt,
the last of the old-timers.

00:16.710 --> 00:21.006
My name is Jack Crabb.

00:21.048 --> 00:25.843
And I am the sole white survivor

00:25.885 --> 00:29.096
of the Battle
of Little Big Horn...

00:29.138 --> 00:31.098
uh... uh...

00:31.140 --> 00:36.896
popularly known
as Custer's Last Stand.

00:36.937 --> 00:38.939
Well...

00:38.981 --> 00:42.818
Mr. Crabb, I'm more interested

00:42.818 --> 00:46.447
in the primitive lifestyle
of the Plains Indian

00:46.489 --> 00:49.741
than I am in the...

00:49.783 --> 00:54.871
tall tales about Custer.

00:54.913 --> 00:58.333
Tall tales?!

00:58.333 --> 01:00.627
Are you calling me a liar?

01:00.668 --> 01:01.711
- No, no...
- Huh?

01:01.753 --> 01:04.381
No, it's just that...

01:04.422 --> 01:08.176
I'm interested
in the way of life

01:08.218 --> 01:13.680
of the Indian rather than,
shall we say, adventure.

01:13.722 --> 01:18.685
You think the Battle of Little
Big Horn was... was a...

01:20.229 --> 01:21.647
...was an adventure?

01:22.856 --> 01:24.316
Oh, shit.

01:24.358 --> 01:29.238
Little Big Horn was not
representative of...

01:29.279 --> 01:32.700
encounters between Whites
and Indians, Mr. Crabb.

01:32.700 --> 01:36.954
You see the...
near genocide of the Indian...

01:36.995 --> 01:39.872
The... the... the near what?!

01:39.914 --> 01:40.998
Near genocide.

01:42.792 --> 01:47.296
It means: "extermination;

01:49.298 --> 01:52.385
the killing off
of an entire people."

01:52.427 --> 01:56.514
That's practically
what we did to the Indian.

01:56.556 --> 02:01.519
But of course, I wouldn't expect
an old Indian fighter like you

02:01.602 --> 02:07.816
to agree with me.

02:07.858 --> 02:09.067
Turn that thing on.

02:09.109 --> 02:10.818
I beg your pardon?

02:10.860 --> 02:12.821
I said, turn that thing on

02:12.863 --> 02:15.449
and shut up.

02:19.119 --> 02:22.873
Now you just set there,
and you'll learn something.

02:25.000 --> 02:31.172
I knowed General
George Armstrong Custer

02:31.213 --> 02:34.842
for what he was.

02:34.884 --> 02:41.932
And I also knowed the Indians...
for what they was.

02:46.437 --> 02:54.778
111 years ago,
when I was ten years old,

02:54.778 --> 03:02.619
my family...
in crossin' the Great Plains...

03:02.660 --> 03:09.709
was wiped out
by a band of wild Indians.

